I have decided to.... make another overarching struct over cst.

this new struct will collect csts in lists and pipelines until it hits a different depth
it has a next pointer that will point to a node with a bracket

we will call it a t_shlist

cst_init guarantees that '(' tokens are within the first few nodes, NOT INCLUDING redirections,
and that ')' are within the last few right before a list operator (|| &&)
in order to collect these redirections properly, redirections matching the old depth level:
		in the node containing the '(' open bracket
		in the node after the corresponding ')' close bracket
	are removed from those nodes and placed in shlist

how exactly we arrange this stuff?

take for example ls && ((echo a || echo b) && echo c)

which produces:
	[ls, &&]
	[(, (, echo, a, ||]
	[echo, b, ), &&]
	[echo, c, )]
shlist 1 takes the first cst and points to the second
shlist 2 removes an open bracket, taking it for itself, and points to the second cst
shlist 3 takes the other open bracket, and the second and third csts, removing the close bracket to count depth
shlist 2 wakes up after shlist 3 finishes, and takes the fourth cst

this implementation will require that each cst have a int field 'sequence' for shlist to use. gud enuf.
each shlist is envisioned to be a complete subshell command list, where it stores its own global redirects
